n people are stranded on an island, each with their weight. Max per boat is 2 people and a boat sustains < W weight. Minimum number of boats to save everyone simultaneously?

Input:
weights vector
W (max supported weight)

Output:
minimum boats number

Solution:
A Greedy approach is used. The weights vector is sorted, for O(nlogn) time complexity, then it is iterated over.
2 iterators traverse w (i from the left and j from the right). When the combined weight on the left + right exceeds W, only the heavier person gets a boat, j decrements. Otherwise, both the heavy and slim people are matched and put in a boat, i increments and j decrements.
The number of boats is incremented in both cases, as well as the third, when i can become equal with j because of a person who cannot be compared anymore.

Complexity:

T: O(nlogn) // sort + for loop with O(n)
S: O(1) // no structures used
